    <section class="section-medium">
      <h3 id="decide-what-you-want-to-know"><span class="label-tag">1</span>Decide what you want to know</h3>
      <p>Try to be as specific as you can about exactly what information you want.</p>
      <p>Start by thinking what issue or problem you are concerned about. Then think about what records or data the authority might hold that could contain information that you are interested in.</p>
      <p>If you are not entirely sure what records might exist, don’t worry, you can describe the general topic of the request. The FOI officer who responds to your request has a duty to provide advice and assistance.</p>
      <p>Here are a few examples of requests:</p>

      <div class="card card-red">
        <div class="card-header"><strong>Problem:</strong></div>
        <p>You are worried about how safe your local park is at night.</p>
      </div>

